'''''Klondike Adventure''''' is a video game published in 1982 by [[SoftSide]] for the [[Atari 8-bit computers]]. It was the February 1982 Adventure of the Month, and the ninth in the series.<ref name="Kottwitz1982"/>

==Contents==
''Klondike Adventure'' is a text-based adventure game in which the player must recover five missing treasures from the arctic.<ref name="SG"/>

==Reception==
Bruce Campbell reviewed ''Klondike Adventure'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 61.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last=Campbell |first=Bruce |date=March 1983 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=61|pages=41}}</ref> Campbell commented that "I enjoyed the unique setting as well as the puzzles presented by ''Klondike''. [...] For a relatively simple adventure, ''Klondike'' is a good buy.  If you get stuck, try yelling."<ref name="SG"/>

